cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.AR, cs.COM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the architecture and simulation of cellular networks with mm-wave access. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions the need for increased system rate and resource control. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of ultra-wideband mm-wave band for mobile traffic. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is possible as the paper briefly mentions the latest status of mm-wave devices. 
- cs.COM (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of mobile traffic on the evolution of cellular networks.
